'''Longitude''' is a thought leadership agency headquartered in London, England. It specialises in providing independent advisory, research and content creation services for a number of large [[Business-to-business|B2B]] companies around the world, and in 2018 was partially acquired by the [[Financial Times]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://aboutus.ft.com/en-gb/announcements/financial-times-acquires-majority-stake-in-research-and-content-specialists-longitude//|title=Financial Times acquires majority stake in research and content specialists Longitude|last=|first=|date=|work=Financial Times|access-date=2018-11-19}}</ref>

==Services==
Longitude's core set of services relates to the production of white papers, research reports and supporting digital content across a range of sectors and industries, most notably technology, professional services and financial services, but it also operates in the legal, energy and industrial sectors.

== About the company ==
Longitude was founded in 2011 by Rob Mitchell and James Watson, both former managing editors at the Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU). Gareth Lofthouse, who was Editorial Director for EMEA at the EIU, joined Longitude as managing director at the beginning of 2013.

The company name was inspired by the [[Longitude Prize]] that was established by the British government in 1714, to encourage leading thinkers to devise an innovative method for precisely determining a ship's [[longitude]].

In 2017, the Financial Times ranked it the 408th<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ig.ft.com/ft-1000/|title=The FT 1000: Europe’s fastest-growing companies|website=ig.ft.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> fastest growing company in Europe, as part of the inaugural FT 1000 ranking.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://uk.prweb.com/releases/2017/04/prweb14234205.htm|title=Longitude scores highly in the FT’s ranking of Europe’s fastest growing companies|work=PRWeb|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref> In 2016, the company was selected as a Leap 100<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/leap-100/2016|title=Leap 100 {{!}} City A.M.|website=www.cityam.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-16}}</ref>  high-growth UK company by City A.M. and Mishcon de Reya.

In February 2018, the Financial Times - acquired a majority stake in Longitude,<ref name=":0" /> making the agency part of the FT group.

